      "conversation_uuid": "c0000003-1701-4d00-8000-00000000c003",
      "message_index": null,
      "entire_chat": "/chat/c0000003-1701-4d00-8000-00000000c003",
      "text": "Look up the Klingon greeting \"nuqneH\" and propose a respectful opening line for a diplomatic dispatch to Chancellor K'mpec.\n<details><summary>Thinking</summary>\n\n> \"nuqneH\" literally means \"what do you want\" — it's blunt by Federation standards but standard among Klingons. I should fetch a phrasebook to confirm register before recommending an opening.\n\n</details>\n<details><summary>Tool use: web_fetch — Fetching: Klingon language reference</summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"url\": \"https://memory-alpha.test/wiki/Klingon_language\"\n}\n```\n</details>\nFor a dispatch to Chancellor K'mpec, open with \"qaleghneS, Chancellor — nuqneH?\" (\"I am honored to see you — what do you want?\"). The honorific softens the bluntness of nuqneH; together they read as warm-but-direct, which Klingons respect.\n<details><summary>Tool result: web_fetch</summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"is_missing\": false,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"site_domain\": \"memory-alpha.test\"\n  },\n  \"text\": \"nuqneH (lit. \\\"what do you want\\\") is the standard Klingon greeting. In formal diplomatic contexts it is paired with the honorific \\\"qaleghneS\\\" (\\\"I am honored to see you\\\").\",\n  \"title\": \"Klingon language — Memory Alpha (test mirror)\",\n  \"type\": \"knowledge\",\n  \"url\": \"https://memory-alpha.test/wiki/Klingon_language\"\n}\n```\n\n</details>\nPerfect. Make it so.",
      "slack_link": null,
